<subSubSection id="6B816545FF980429FF52614B823ED5F2" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="232436CEFF980429FF52614B81DCD54D" blockId="5.[151,415,1120,1146]" box="[151,415,1120,1146]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<heading id="786C81A2FF980429FF52614B81DCD54D" bold="true" box="[151,415,1120,1146]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" reason="1">
<emphasis id="11EFEADCFF980429FF52614B81DCD54D" bold="true" box="[151,415,1120,1146]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
The 
<taxonomicName id="E49B4D4DFF980429FF0A614B810FD54D" box="[207,332,1120,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymans">
<emphasis id="11EFEADCFF980429FF0A614B810FD54D" bold="true" box="[207,332,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">lacrymans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="232436CEFF980429FF526180823ED5F2" blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" box="[151,637,1195,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
The 
<taxonomicName id="E49B4D4DFF980429FF0E61808106D5F3" box="[203,325,1195,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymans">
<emphasis id="11EFEADCFF980429FF0E61808106D5F3" box="[203,325,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">lacrymans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group is characterized by:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6B816545FF980429FF5261F8817FD71A" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="232436CEFF980429FF5261F88367D5DA" blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" box="[151,804,1235,1261]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<number id="955324E9FF980429FF5261F880E5D5DA" box="[151,166,1235,1261]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
First flagellomere subrectangular with dorsal arista.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="232436CEFF980429FF5261D081C6D452" blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<number id="955324E9FF980429FF5261D080E5D422" box="[151,166,1275,1301]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="2.0">2</number>
Vein M with an almost right angle bend between dm-cu crossvein and apex (
<figureCitation id="BBA02A4BFF980429FB8D61D084C8D422" box="[1096,1163,1275,1301]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[266,1333,194,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[249,1344,184,1732]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mesorhaga lacrymans Parent: a. hypopygium, left lateral. b. male distal tarsus I, dorsal. c. male wing, dorsal. M. cocori n. sp.: d. hypopygium, left lateral. M. sarukhani n. sp.: e. hypopygium, left lateral. M. funebris Parent: f. hypopygium, left lateral. M. hule n. sp.: g. hypopygium, left lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175600/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="955324E9FF980429FBBA61D084C8D422" box="[1151,1163,1275,1301]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
c). 
<specimenCount id="359DFD47FF980429FF526008814DD40A" box="[151,270,1315,1341]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="male">
<number id="955324E9FF980429FF52600880E5D40A" box="[151,166,1315,1341]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="3.0">3</number>
Males
</specimenCount>
and females often with large area of brown infuscation on wing (
<figureCitation id="BBA02A4BFF980429FBCF6008840FD40A" box="[1034,1100,1315,1341]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[266,1333,194,1711]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[249,1344,184,1732]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mesorhaga lacrymans Parent: a. hypopygium, left lateral. b. male distal tarsus I, dorsal. c. male wing, dorsal. M. cocori n. sp.: d. hypopygium, left lateral. M. sarukhani n. sp.: e. hypopygium, left lateral. M. funebris Parent: f. hypopygium, left lateral. M. hule n. sp.: g. hypopygium, left lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175600/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number id="955324E9FF980429FB856008840FD40A" box="[1088,1100,1315,1341]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
c), although sometimes faint or appearing smoky.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="232436CEFF980429FF5260588231D4BA" blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" box="[151,626,1395,1421]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<specimenCount id="359DFD47FF980429FF526058814DD4BA" box="[151,270,1395,1421]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="male">
<number id="955324E9FF980429FF52605880E5D4BA" box="[151,166,1395,1421]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="4.0">4</number>
Males
</specimenCount>
sometimes with black halters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="232436CEFF980429FF0360B0817FD71A" blockId="5.[151,1437,1195,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
The 
<taxonomicName id="E49B4D4DFF980429FF3860B08134D483" box="[253,375,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymans">
<emphasis id="11EFEADCFF980429FF3860B08134D483" box="[253,375,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">lacrymans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group comprises four Neotropical species occurring in forests (lowlands to elevations of 
<quantity id="E4639B2BFF980429FF5260E880B1D4EA" box="[151,242,1475,1501]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
) along the Cordillera, and includes 
<taxonomicName id="E49B4D4DFF980429FD5860E8837CD4EB" box="[669,831,1475,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacrymans">
<emphasis id="11EFEADCFF980429FD5860E8837CD4EB" box="[669,831,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. lacrymans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="5B8C765EFF980429FC9560E88390D4EA" box="[848,979,1475,1501]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="5B8C765EFF980429FBCB60E88433D4EA" box="[1038,1136,1475,1501]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Panama</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="E49B4D4DFF980429FB4160E884B4D4EB" box="[1156,1271,1475,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cocori">
<emphasis id="11EFEADCFF980429FB4160E884B4D4EB" box="[1156,1271,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. cocori</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="5B8C765EFF980429FACD60E885CCD4EA" box="[1288,1423,1475,1501]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="E49B4D4DFF980429FF5260C080B0D733" box="[151,243,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hule">
<emphasis id="11EFEADCFF980429FF5260C080B0D733" box="[151,243,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. hule</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="5B8C765EFF980429FEC360C081CCD732" box="[262,399,1515,1541]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName id="E49B4D4DFF980429FE6360C08205D733" box="[422,582,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sarukhani">
<emphasis id="11EFEADCFF980429FE6360C08205D733" box="[422,582,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. sarukhani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="5B8C765EFF980429FD9D60C082A2D732" box="[600,737,1515,1541]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="E49B4D4DFF980429FCE860C083F4D733" box="[813,951,1515,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Mesorhaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis id="11EFEADCFF980429FCE860C083F4D733" box="[813,951,1515,1540]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. funebris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="5B8C765EFF980429FC0F60C08447D732" box="[970,1028,1515,1541]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5B8C765EFF980429FBD660C08436D732" box="[1043,1141,1515,1541]" name="Ecuador" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="5B8C765EFF980429FB7160C08571D732" box="[1204,1330,1515,1541]" name="Venezuela" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
). All are treated below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
